# Module Architecture Patterns

## Module Structure

Each feature module in `src/modules/` follows a consistent structure:

```
modules/
  {module-name}/
    types.d.ts         # TypeScript type definitions (exports to 'Types' module)
```

## Module Organization Rules

- **Type definitions**: Use `types.d.ts` to declare types in the global `Types` module namespace
- **Referencing types**: Import types from `Types` module: `import { TUser } from 'Types'`

## Example Module Structure

Reference the `state` module as the canonical example:

- `@src/modules/state/types.d.ts` - Type definitions

## Styling

- Glyph is our design system. When creating new foundational components (text, button, icons, etc) keep them in Glyph folder.
- use CSS modules for styling.
- don't use Tailwind or any other 3rd party CSS framework
- you can use atomic styles from Glyph (src/glyph/common.css)
- use `cn` function from Glyph when you need apply certain class conditionally.
